Still, that may not be enough: the most valuable sports properties Fox owns=
 =E2=80=94 the NFL and Big Ten =E2=80=94 are on the broadcast network for e=
ither all of their games (the NFL) or their most prominent ones (the Big Te=
n); FS1=E2=80=99s college slate may not be enough to hold down the fort. Th=
at, by extension, makes me wonder if Fox ought not bid for the NBA in parti=
cular and put it on FS1; CEO Lachlan Murdoch said in May ( https://thestrea=
mable.com/news/fox-ceo-has-no-interest-in-nba-rights-giving-nbc-even-more-l=
everage-to-land-broadcast-deal ) that the company didn=E2=80=99t have any i=
nterest, but I wonder if Disney=E2=80=99s insistence on taking ESPN over-th=
e-top might change his mind.

Keep in mind that the real moneymaker for Fox is retransmission fees (for F=
ox) and affiliate fees (primarily for Fox News); retransmission fees don=E2=
=80=99t exist if viewers use an antenna, and Fox News is the epitome of a c=
hannel that captures affiliate fees from the entire bundle base because its=
 fans will change their TV service to get it. Of course Charter just showed=
 the increased fragility of that strategy, but the broader point is that ke=
eping the bundle viable is still Fox=E2=80=99s number one priority; if ESPN=
 isn=E2=80=99t going to lend a hand then it may fall on Murdoch to make a b=
ig sports deal that doesn=E2=80=99t make sense individually but is good for=
 the company as a whole, just like his father did with the NFL thirty years=
 ago.

Disney=E2=80=99s Taylor Swift Era Confirmed
-----------------------------------

From the Wall Street Journal ( https://www.wsj.com/business/media/disney-to=
-invest-60-billion-in-theme-parks-cruises-over-next-decade-6fc87426 ) :

Disney plans to spend about $60 billion to expand its theme parks, cruise l=
ines and resorts over the next decade, almost doubling its investment in a =
division that provides its primary source of profits. Chief Executive Bob I=
ger and Josh D=E2=80=99Amaro, chief of the company=E2=80=99s Parks, Experie=
nces and Products division, unveiled the plans =E2=80=94 which were light o=
n details of specific projects =E2=80=94 at an investor summit held at Walt=
 Disney World in Orlando this week. The company outlined the planned invest=
ment in a filing Tuesday morning with the Securities and Exchange Commissio=
n.

The market wasn=E2=80=99t pleased, sending Disney=E2=80=99s stock down 3.6%=
, and I get it; I wrote in the conclusion of Disney=E2=80=99s Taylor Swift =
Era ( https://stratechery.com/2023/disneys-taylor-swift-era/?access_token=
=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6InN0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5LnBhc3Nwb3J0Lm9ubGluZSIsInR5=
cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJhdWQiOiJzdHJhdGVjaGVyeS5wYXNzcG9ydC5vbmxpbmUiLCJhenAiOiJIS0=
xjUzREd1Nod1AyWURLYmZQV00xIiwiZW50Ijp7InVyaSI6WyJodHRwczovL3N0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5L=
mNvbS8yMDIzL2Rpc25leXMtdGF5bG9yLXN3aWZ0LWVyYS8iXX0sImV4cCI6MTY5NzgwNDczOSwi=
aWF0IjoxNjk1MjEyNzM5LCJpc3MiOiJodHRwczovL2FwaS5wYXNzcG9ydC5vbmxpbmUvb2F1dGg=
iLCJzY29wZSI6ImZlZWQ6cmVhZCBhcnRpY2xlOnJlYWQgYXNzZXQ6cmVhZCBjYXRlZ29yeTpyZW=
FkIGVudGl0bGVtZW50cyIsInN1YiI6IlJzZXVZRThqZ0hlUHBXSmYxZkFiNEMiLCJ1c2UiOiJhY=
2Nlc3MifQ.DYL_ExC5Mj5rJcUJSb8KHabcy9VNYvs84XSyQpty28vqVKctd5pjKJzGurEYDDN7k=
qUBCxDtkaS1qczLm7E5pfdd2JWsq-rZB8LUmtXI-wFx6wnfcfkNEFyueU0C2BDSRw92Ezqv5bii=
