hvsZVi8ghenhublvTbqj3g5zfQ9ir4V_t95JgDetiDBl8TnW_pgbO34i0xXvYP8bjjRdMlBIO1T=
mYa7_EsjFsuLJccVP1frQRwV_t8LSaZZajBYXh13760O2HhlxBFA ) :

The end result is the inversion you see in Disney=E2=80=99s recent results.=
 Disney is, from this point forward, not much different than Taylor Swift: =
sure, there is money to be made (hopefully) in areas like streaming, but th=
e real durable value and outsized profits will come from real life experien=
ces. This is, to be sure, a good business, but it has its limits: it is rem=
arkable that Swift performed six shows in seven nights in Los Angeles, but =
it was still only six shows; concerts don=E2=80=99t scale like CD sales use=
d to. Disney, similarly, only has so many theme parks, that only accommodat=
e so many people, and operating those theme parks takes significant ongoing=
 resources.

More parks and cruises are good! Spending $60 billion to develop them is, r=
elative to the leverage inherent in the old TV model, not so good, particul=
arly since they will, by definition, be capacity constrained. Apparently so=
me number of investors, though, have yet to accept this reality.

The good news for Disney is that their stock has taken such a beating over =
the reality of this transition that there is probably significant room to m=
aneuver; MoffettNathanson used Travel & Leisure comps to value Disney=E2=80=
=99s parks and consumer products business at $164.4 billion last earnings, =
while the company=E2=80=99s current market cap is $150 billion. In other wo=
rds, to the extent Michael Nathanson=E2=80=99s valuation is correct, you=E2=
=80=99re getting the movie, streaming, and TV businesses for negative $14.4=
 billion!

This is not, to be clear, a stock recommendation, but rather an acknowledgm=
ent that the interesting thing about the Charter-Disney fight is that while=
 Charter won because they had nothing to lose, Disney, at least in terms of=
 valuation, wasn=E2=80=99t that far behind. Too bad Iger didn=E2=80=99t wai=
t to return to the company until now: there is no where to go but up, and t=
he freedom to do basically whatever is necessary to do so.

